Tariffs and geopolitical uncertainty clouding the outlook
Geopolitics & Markets Shifting trade flows
 Erosion of rules-based world order  Pause in client activity amid tariff
and multilateralism uncertainty
 Shift toward a multipolar world  Reconfiguration of trade, payment and
tech links
 Diversification of trade currencies
and reserve assets
3

Impact of tariffs
Global challenges Opportunities for DBS
 Trade disruption  Trade shifts – supply chain, working
capital, alternative payment flows
 Global growth slowdown
 New growth corridors and sectors
 Interest rate uncertainty
 Casa growth if rates fall
 Weaker market sentiment
 Continued wealth inflows
 Credit stresses
 Trading opportunities and client
hedging demand
4

2025 outlook

Business momentum resilient in April, but risk from heightened uncertainty

Group net interest income slightly above 2024 levels based on three rate cuts
Lower Group NIM, offset by balance sheet growth
o
Markets trading to benefit from lower funding cost
o
Funding to be deployed into non-loan assets if loan demand weakens
o

Commercial book non-interest income growth to be mid-to high-single digits

Cost-income ratio to be in low-40% range

SP assumed to normalise to 17-20bp; GP reserves provide buffer

Net profit to be below 2024 levels, mainly due to global minimum tax of 15%
